    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bush's Road Out of the Balkans</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Reihan Morshed Salam letter contends withdrawal from Balkans is only realistic option for US (Oct 24 editorial)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>If America's role in the Balkans is, as you suggest (editorial, Oct. 24), to provide ''enough security for displaced refugees to return to their homes or for elections to take place without the risk of physical intimidation,'' then nothing short of imperialism will do. Only a long-term commitment can begin to undo the damage wrought by ethnic hatred.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>If America's role in the Balkans is, as you suggest (editorial, Oct. 24), to provide ''enough security for displaced refugees to return to their homes or for elections to take place without the risk of physical intimidation,'' then nothing short of imperialism will do. Only a long-term commitment can begin to undo the damage wrought by ethnic hatred.</p>
        <p>Without such a commitment, ethnic tensions will be resolved through ''ethnic cleansing.'' In this era of declining military budgets and declining American resolve, withdrawal is our only option.</p>
        <p>REIHAN MORSHED SALAM  Cambridge, Mass., Oct. 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
